text: "L'invasion russe de l'Ukraine" est une "violation" du droit international, a insist√© le secr√©taire g√©n√©ral de l'ONU lors d'une rencontre avec Vladimir Poutine. Antonio Guterres, qui a rencontr√© le pr√©sident russe jeudi 24 octobre en marge du sommet des Brics √† Kazan, en Russie, "a r√©p√©t√©" cette position, selon un communiqu√© du bureau du porte-parole du secr√©taire g√©n√©ral diffus√© √† New York, r√©p√©tant √©galement son soutien √† une "paix juste" en accord avec la charte et le droit international.Le chef de l'ONU a d'autre part soulign√© au pr√©sident russe son attachement √† "la libert√© de navigation en mer Noire", capitale pour l'Ukraine et la s√©curit√© alimentaire et √©nerg√©tique mondiale. title: Vermont Trooper Archer: A Beacon of Bravery Amid Freezing Waters
text:

Vermont Trooper Archer: A Beacon of Bravery Amid Freezing Waters
In a gripping display of valor, Vermont State Trooper Michelle Archer emerged as a beacon of hope and bravery when an 8-year-old girl plummeted through the ice of a freezing pond. The incident, which occurred on December 17, was captured on film, showcasing the courageous act of Archer, who did not hesitate to dive into the icy waters to save the child.
Swift Rescue Amid Freezing Waters
Upon receiving the distress call about two children having fallen into the icy pond, Archer responded promptly. The 8-year-old and her 6-year-old sibling were playing near the pond when the fragile ice gave way beneath them. While a nearby homeowner was able to rescue the younger child, the older one remained trapped in the chilling waters. That‚Äôs when Trooper Archer arrived on the scene, diving into the freezing pond without a second thought, and successfully retrieving the girl from the frosty depths.
Heroic Conduct Earns Recognition
Archer‚Äôs swift and selfless actions, combined with the assistance of Trooper Keith Cote and the helpful homeowner, saved the girl‚Äôs life. In recognition of their heroic deeds, Archer and Cote, along with the homeowner, have been recommended for the agency‚Äôs Lifesaving Award. The body camera footage of the rescue has won widespread praise, highlighting the remarkable courage of the troopers and the homeowner involved.
The Aftermath and a Reminder
Miraculously, the girl, initially facing life-threatening injuries, made a complete recovery following the incident and has since returned home. This event underscores the dangers associated with icy ponds during cold weather and emphasizes the critical importance of quick, decisive action in emergencies. It also serves as a stark reminder that the bravery and selflessness of individuals like Trooper Archer can make the difference between life and death.

author: Joel B. Pollak
title: Jewish Groups Slam Biden Executive Order on Settlers: 'Will Embolden Terrorism'
text:
Jewish groups and legal experts are slamming President Joe Biden‚Äôs executive order Thursday applying sanctions against what the White House calls ‚Äúextremist settler violence‚Äù in the West Bank, saying that it effectively encourages moreHamas terrorism.
As Breitbart News reported , Biden issued the executive order as he was en route to Michigan, a key swing state in the election, with a large Arab and Muslim population. Leaders of those groups have threatened not to vote for Biden in 2024 because of his perceived support for Israel in the war against Hamas, which started when Hamas launched a terror attack against Israel on October 7. (As Breitbart News has noted, many leading voices in those communities are themselves ‚Äú extremist ‚Äù on the issue.)
The order would apply financial sanctions to individuals committing acts of violence in the West Bank (known to many Israelis as Judea and Samaria), who are already subject to prosecution and punishment under Israeli law.
But the executive order goes much further than that. It could also be used to sanction political leaders and political parties with no direct link to violence; it could also be used to sanction anyone who verbally defends settlers accused of violence.
The language of the executive order claims, without evidence, that settler violence has reached ‚Äúhigh levels.‚Äù In fact, Israeli officials say, it has declined. Statistically, there are also many times more attacks by Palestinians against Jews than vice versa.
As Israeli legal scholar Eugene Kontorovich notes, the order ‚Äúdoes not require acts of violence ‚Äî anyone vaguely involved in doing or not doing anything the [White House] thinks undermines ‚Äòpeace‚Äô and ‚Äòsecurity'‚Äù can be punished. It is also only being applied to Israeli Jews ‚Äî not to Palestinians ‚Äî even though the Palestinian Authority actively encourages violence against Jews through the ‚Äúpay-to-slay‚Äù policy, which gives stipends to terrorists imprisoned in Israel, and pensions to the families of dead terrorists.
The new sanctions tools against Israelis announced by the Biden Administration is not about settler violence. First, it does not require acts of violence ‚Äì anyone vaguely involved in doing or not doing anything the WH thinks undermines ‚Äúpeace‚Äù and ‚Äúsecurity‚Äù in WB qualifies.
As‚Ä¶
‚Äî Eugene Kontorovich (@EVKontorovich) February 1, 2024
The Republican Jewish Coalition (RJC) issued a blistering statement, noting that Biden‚Äôs executive order created a false moral equivalence between Hamas and Israeli settlers, the overwhelming majority of whom are peaceful and law-abiding. The RJC said:
Biden has to know that this executive order will be taken by many as suggesting a moral equivalence between Hamas terrorists, who massacred, raped, and kidnapped defenseless civilians, and a small number of Israelis whose reported actions are investigated and prosecuted where appropriate by the authorities.
Let‚Äôs be clear: we stand unequivocally against criminal violence ‚Äì there is no moral equivalence because there can be no equivalence between a democracy governed by the rule of law and a brutally corrupt terrorist organization.
This first-of-its-kind executive order sends precisely the wrong message at absolutely the worst time, emboldening the terrorists and undermining the Jewish state. Joe Biden has needlessly damaged the US-Israel alliance yet again.
Yaakov Katz, former editor of the Jerusalem Post , called the executive order a ‚Äúterrible mistake‚Äù that ‚Äúis meant to create a moral equivalency between Hamas and Jewish attacks‚Äù and showed a ‚Äúdeep confusion‚Äù within the White House. He added :
Hamas is a terrorist organization that rules Gaza, has tens of thousands of fighters and is in possession of tens of thousands of rockets. It has massacred over 1,000 Israelis and is state run. The other is a tiny fringe and scattered group of people that has maybe at the most been involved in a handful of violent incidents that are mostly still under investigation.
These violent settlers should all be arrested and tried by Israel, but to issue this executive order now and to impose sanctions is to try and tell a story of how the US is tough on both sides.
Keep in mind that Biden is off to Michigan today, home to the largest Arab population in the US. Michigan is a swing state. This is about politics.
More importantly though, there are not two sides here and this is the mistake that Biden is making. He is sending a dangerous message to the world, one that will sadly embolden terrorism.
Historian Sara Yael Hirshhorn seconded Katz‚Äôs analysis, saying that ‚Äúit‚Äôs clear the Biden admin has little internal understanding of the phenonemon.‚Äù
Co-sign @yaakovkatz !
As prof who studies settlers & likewise has zero-tolerance for settler terrorism, it‚Äôs clear the Biden admin has little internal understanding of the phenonemon. This won‚Äôt deter attacks or violent rhetoric ‚Äì if anything will only amp up in the short-term: https://t.co/uIq9O5xSHI
‚Äî Dr. Sara Yael Hirschhorn (@SaraHirschhorn1) February 1, 2024
According to the Times of Israel, the executive order is so broad that it could be used to ‚Äúcut off the entire settler movement from US financial services,‚Äù in the view of S. Daniel Abraham Center for Middle East Peace managing director Joel Braunold.
That has long been a goal of the ‚ÄúBoycott, Divestment, and Sanctions‚Äù (BDS) movement, which has long sought to target the Jewish communities in Judea and Samara. Likewise, the left-wing group J Street, which often adopts anti-Israel positions, and which sought as early as 2009 to urge the U.S. Treasury to investigate Jewish non-profit groups allocating charitable contributions to projects in Judea and Samaria, welcomed Biden‚Äôs executive order.
In a press release, J Street made the exact moral equivalency that critics warned about: ‚ÄúJust as the United States has rightly doubled down on sanctioning terrorists and terror organizations like Hamas and Hezbollah that have targeted Israelis for decades, so too must it take steps against those who engage in terrorism against Palestinians,‚Äù J Street said, calling for sanctions to be ‚Äúvigorously and consistently enforced.‚Äù
The controversy recalls the outrage over the outgoing Obama-Biden administration‚Äôs decision to allow the United Nations Security Council to pass a resolution in 2016 declaring the Israeli presence ‚Äî including in the Jewish Quarter of Jerusalem ‚Äî to be illegal under international law. President Donald Trump responded, upon taking office, by visiting the Jewish Quarter and the Western Wall, the holiest site in Judaism, becoming the first sitting U.S. president to do so, affirming Israeli sovereignty there.
Joel B. Pollak is Senior Editor-at-Large at Breitbart News and the host of Breitbart News Sunday on Sirius XM Patriot on Sunday evenings from 7 p.m. to 10 p.m. ET (4 p.m. to 7 p.m. PT). He is the author of the 2021 e-book, ‚Äú The Zionist Conspiracy (and how to join it) ,‚Äù now updated with a new foreword. He is also the author of the recent e-book, Neither Free nor Fair: The 2020 U.S. Presidential Election . He is a winner of the 2018 Robert Novak Journalism Alumni Fellowship. Follow him on Twitter at @joelpollak .

author: Michael Grullon
title: BRICS: China, Russia Completely Ditch US Dollar For Trade
text: BRICS members Russia and China have abandoned the use of Western currencies, including the US Dollar, in their bilateral trade. According to Russian Prime Minister Mikhail Mishustin, the business ties between the two nations are booming, with bilateral trade turnover already reaching ‚Äú$200 billion ahead of schedule.‚Äù Last week, the Russian leader spoke about the BRICS de-dollarization mission, in particular Russia‚Äôs involvement. Mishustin said nearly all payments were being carried out in Rubles and Yuan. ‚ÄúWe continue to increase the share of national currencies in mutual settlements. If in 2020 this figure was about 20 percent, then this year we have completely gotten rid of the currencies of third countries in mutual settlements,‚Äù Mishustin was quoted as saying by Russian media. Also Read: BRICS: Russia & India Settle $40B of Trade in Local Currency Russia and China‚Äôs trade ties have only strengthened in the past year, with the two BRICS nations working on multiple deals in their local currencies. In [October](https://watcher.guru/news/brics-russia-china-agree-to-25b-deal-in-local-currency), the two powerhouses made a $25 billion deal in local currencies to increase trade dealings in the food and energy sectors. BRICS has fully embraced de-dollarization since Western sanctions were placed against Russia. ‚ÄúWe are creating comfortable conditions for the work of commercial firms on the Russian and Chinese markets. We have an extensive joint agenda,‚Äù Mishustin added in a speech last week. Russia Pushing For More Inter-BRICS Trade Outside of de-dollarization, [Russia](https://watcher.guru/news/brics-iran-russia-officially-ditch-us-dollar-for-trade) is also leading the initiative for BRICS to increase relations and trade within the bloc. Both [Russia and India](https://tvbrics.com/en/news/trade-volume-between-russia-and-india-exceeded-over-40-billion-in-the-first-three-quarters-of-this-y/#:~:text=According%20to%20Volvach%2C%20trade%20volume,supply%20of%20goods%20from%20India.) have settled $40 billion worth of trade in local currency, and the remaining nations are also already working on building up their trade relationships with one another. [Also Read: 5 Major Countries to Join BRICS Alliance in 2024](https://watcher.guru/news/5-major-countries-to-join-brics-alliance-in-2024) Furthermore, last week Russian Finance Minister Anton Siluanov spoke at the Russia-China Financial Dialogue forum in Beijing. There, he further pushed for trade within the bloc as well as a unified BRICS pay system. ‚ÄúWe need to further develop financial cooperation within the BRICS countries. Here we see opportunities to develop a payments system that would be independent of the infrastructure, which does not always fully fulfill the goals of individual countries,‚Äù Siluanov stated.

author: world today news
title: vivo X Fold3 Pro Review: The Ultimate Foldable Phone Competing with Candy Bar Flagships - An In-Depth Analysis - World Today News
text:
vivo X Fold3 Pro reviewÔΩúAn all-round foldable phone with no blind spots that can compete with candy bar flagships
While other horizontal foldable phones are vying to set new records for thinness and lightness, vivo‚Äôs first two generations of X Fold products chose to put comprehensive functions first among the trade-offs. The development concept of ‚Äúflagship first, folding later‚Äù has won a good reputation among pragmatic consumers for X Fold/X Fold+ and X Fold2. But while the experience is balanced, they still lack a bit of a surprising feeling, and this is often something that many people find difficult to ignore for a new type of thing called folding machines.
Under this premise, the third generation of vivo‚Äôs discount phone debuts with a completely new look. Although the standard model X Fold3 has some reservations in terms of specifications, it directly reaches a weight and (unfolded) thickness of 219g and 4.65mm. The thinness and lightness can only be described as ‚Äúoutrageous‚Äù. The X Fold3 Pro, which is still positioned as an all-rounder, actually only weighs 236g and is 5.2mm thick. It is ‚Äúarmed‚Äù by Snapdragon 8 Gen 3, 5,700mAh semi-solid-state battery, internal and external ultrasonic fingerprints, and periscope cameras, which is undoubtedly more likely to arouse people‚Äôs interest. After using it, I think it is even qualified to be compared with candy bar flagships.
Appearance and feel vivo X Fold3 Pro review
The appearance of vivo X Fold3 Pro combines X Fold2 Similar to the characteristics of the X100 series, the ring decoration around the circular camera area has a strong presence, and the small metal edge on the edge of the hinge echoes the splicing design on the back of the X Fold2. The new phone comes in two colors: black and white. The white model I have on the back has a marble-like dark pattern on the back, which exudes a low-key luxury. The material used is UPE fiber, which is hot-pressed from high-strength fiber and glass fiber and can provide stronger toughness and impact resistance than ordinary glass. At the same time, this material also helps reduce the weight of the phone, and its touch feel is close to that of matte glass. It is very delicate, does not leave fingerprints, but is a little slippery.
As a user who switched from X Fold2, I can clearly feel the difference in weight and thickness as soon as I pick up X Fold3 Pro. The surroundings of the device have been carefully polished, and the center of gravity is properly arranged, making the X Fold3 Pro quite comfortable to hold. You can still find the dedicated mute lever on the side of the phone, and the inner and outer dual ultrasonic fingerprints are also retained. When evaluating the previous generation, I personally thought these two points were very good points. The regret that X Fold2 lacks waterproofing has finally been made up for by vivo. The waterproof rating of X Fold3 Pro has reached IPX8, which puts it on the same starting line as popular folding phones such as Huawei Mate X5 and Samsung Galaxy Z Fold5.
Screen and sound quality vivo X Fold3 Pro review
The inner and outer screen sizes of this new phone remain the same as those of the X Fold 2, still 8.03 inches and 6.53 inches. The ratios are 4:3.55 and 21.1:9 respectively, which are basically unchanged. The refresh rate remains at 120Hz, but the resolution has been increased to 2,480√ó2,200 and 2,748√ó1,172. Unlike the previous generation, which used Samsung panels both inside and outside, X Fold3 Pro chose a combination of Samsung E7 on the inside and BOE Q9+ OLED on the outside. Fortunately, vivo has adjusted the display consistency quite well. The theoretical peak brightness of the inner screen can reach 4,500 nits, which is enough to cope with outdoor environments in actual use.
There is no problem with the color accuracy of the two panels. There is a small pity that the PPI of the two panels is not unified (412 inside and 457 outside). The hinge of X Fold3 Pro still has a water-drop design, but the material is replaced by ultra-light carbon fiber, which is 37% lighter than the previous generation solution. The surface of the inner screen is covered with UTG ultra-thin glass, and no plastic film with poor experience is chosen to reduce weight. The crease is still slightly palpable, but it may not be visible if you don‚Äôt look carefully every day. There is no gap between the two halves of the machine after folding. The official claims that it can achieve ‚Äú500,000 folds without worry‚Äù, but this cannot be verified in a short period of time (for reference, the author did not encounter this problem when using the first two generations of X Fold any malfunction).
vivo X Fold3 Pro review
In terms of personal listening experience, the dual speakers of X Fold3 Pro are a bit backward compared to X Fold2. Many people may feel that this is not a strong perception. From vivo‚Äôs perspective, it is reasonable to ‚Äúuse the knife‚Äù in this aspect in pursuit of thinness and frivolity. As a product equipped with Qualcomm chips, X Fold3 Pro does not encounter the dilemma of not having its own high-end true wireless headphones like the X100 Pro. Vivo launched the TWS 4 series of headphones for it at the same time. The Hi-Fi version supports LDAC and aptX Lossless and can achieve 55dB active noise reduction. It should be the best choice for X Fold3 Pro users to buy headphones at present.
camera vivo X Fold3 Pro review
The camera system of the Lenses and related functions, as well as vivo‚Äôs self-developed V3 imaging chip. Compared with the previous generation, the most enhanced feature is the telephoto capability. The existence of the periscope module and the floating lens group makes telephoto shooting both practical and interesting.
vivo X Fold3 Pro real shot samples
At the 70mm focal length, the device‚Äôs image quality is very solid. The imaging is clear and detailed, and it still has good usability in low-light environments and even when the digital zoom is up to 10X. The macro mode of this camera provides two options: native 3X and cropped magnification to 6X, and its focusing performance is satisfactory. It also provides a great degree of freedom in simulated blur, allowing you to further highlight the subject. At focal lengths below 70mm, the algorithm mainly relies on ‚Äúzoom‚Äù optimization on the images captured by the 23mm main camera. The actual effect is acceptable. Nowadays, it is a general trend for non-imaging flagships to cancel the native camera with a fixed focal length.
Continue reading the story
1 / 46
vivo X Fold3 Pro real shot samples vivo X Fold3 Pro real shot samples
In order to meet the different tone preferences of users, this phone still prepares three modes: vivid, texture, and Zeiss natural color. When shooting portraits, various Zeiss lens simulation effects also bring a lot of playability. The special structure of folding mobile phones also allows users to take pictures in unconventional ways such as waist-level framing and preview (rear) selfies. In addition, with the V3 chip, the progress in 4K 60p recording is impressive. However, the smoothness when switching cameras with continuous zoom is slightly less smooth than that of the X100 Pro, but this may be due to the fact that the early software has not yet been perfected.
system vivo X Fold3 Pro review
Some of the software improvements made by vivo X Fold3 Pro are mainly focused on improving productivity. First of all, vivo‚Äôs blue heart model is further integrated into the OriginOS system (designed for mainland users). It can now use the new tool ‚ÄúLittle V Helper‚Äù to convert your call and meeting recordings into audio and video recordings. Text notes, and also supports English in addition to Chinese. At the same time, the note app has also added AI creative capabilities. You can let AI automatically help you continue writing, polishing or expanding existing content.
When X Fold2 was released, vivo had already established a link between Android and Windows, enabling remote control of PCs on mobile phones. With the launch of a new generation of products, this cross-platform control experience has also been extended to Mac computers. In actual use, the delay in operation is completely acceptable, and sliding, clicking, and input are all very smooth. Moreover, vivo has thoughtfully added macOS function buttons above the phone‚Äôs virtual keyboard, allowing Mac users to use familiar shortcut key combinations on small screens. Even when the computer is in a dormant state, you can still use your mobile phone to start it remotely. In addition, on the mobile phone, the system also adds support for Apple‚Äôs office suites Pages, Keynote and Numbers.
For an Android device, it is worthy of praise for being able to achieve such interoperability with Apple‚Äôs system. It may not be too much to say that vivo ‚Äúhelped‚Äù Apple launch a folding phone!
Performance and battery life vivo X Fold3 Pro review
Like last year‚Äôs vivo X Fold2, this year‚Äôs X Fold3 Pro also won the first discount of Qualcomm‚Äôs flagship chip. With the support of Snapdragon 8 Gen 3, the performance of the device is unmatched among foldable machines. When ‚ÄúGenshin Impact‚Äù turns on high and medium rendering precision, the average frame rate for half an hour of playing on the internal screen can reach close to 55fps and 60fps respectively. There will be a certain amount of warmth on the back of the machine, but overall it is still to an acceptable level.
X Fold3 Pro has a built-in semi-solid battery with a full capacity of 5,700mAh, which is the most discounted phone currently available. It is actually as durable as the numbers look like. During my recent trip to Tokyo, I spent one day intensively shooting, editing images on the screen, using map navigation, and occasionally sharing hotspots. Under such usage conditions, there was never a day when the machine ran out of battery before returning to the hotel. . Even if the battery is low, this phone is protected by 100W wired and 50W wireless fast charging. After being plugged in, it only takes 5 minutes to charge nearly 25% of the battery, and it reaches 100% in about half an hour.
competitors vivo X Fold3 Pro review
Although vivo X Fold3 Pro and X Fold3 have similar appearance, their target customer groups are obviously different, so there should be no room for conflict. The biggest rivals of X Fold3 Pro are probably Huawei‚Äôs Mate X5 and OPPO Find N3 / OnePlus Open. The former has a huge brand belief bonus. Although the latter does not have advantages in performance, power consumption (small battery and no wireless charging), and size, it does have unique features in photography and software interaction, and it has recently lowered its price. price. However, in comparison, I personally think that vivo X Fold3 Pro is still the most comprehensive and balanced choice at present. Competing products that can pose a substantial threat to it may not appear until the second half of the year.
Conclusion vivo X Fold3 Pro review
As mentioned at the beginning, the author feels that vivo X Fold3 Pro is already a product that can compete with candy bar flagships. It has been almost five years since the birth of foldable screen mobile phones. Consumers have to make fewer and fewer compromises to choose them, and we have almost reached that critical turning point. For those who are still waiting to see this type of device, you can think of X Fold3 Pro as the upper limit of the current folding machine field. Its comprehensive degree of completion is already quite high, and the discounted machine is really close to ‚Äúflying into the homes of ordinary people.‚Äù Perhaps the only remaining problem is price, which may soon be solved.

title: Dumpster Rentals Frisco Opens New Location In TX Area
text:
Dumpster Rentals Frisco Opens New Location In TX Area 12-26-2024 11:28 PM CET | Business, Economy, Finances, Banking & Insurance
Press release from: Getnews / PR Agency: Headlineplus
Image: https://www.globalnewslines.com/uploads/2024/12/d5deaaac0d4a61c58c0f09d5a36e022c.jpg
Dumpster Rentals Frisco, a leading provider of residential and commercial dumpster rental services, is excited to announce the opening of its new location in the vibrant Frisco, TX area. The new location will allow the company to better serve the waste management needs of the local community with competitive pricing and exceptional customer service.
With years of experience in the dumpster rental industry, Dumpster Rentals Frisco specializes in providing reliable and efficient waste management solutions for both residential and commercial clients. The company offers a variety of dumpster sizes to accommodate different project needs, from small home cleanouts to large construction projects.
"Opening a new location in Frisco is a significant milestone for us," said Jon Howard, Regional Sales Manager of Dumpster Rentals Frisco. "We are committed to providing top-notch dumpster rental services with competitive pricing to meet the diverse needs of the Frisco community. Our team is dedicated to ensuring a seamless and hassle-free experience for our customers."
Customers can expect the following services from Dumpster Rentals Frisco:
- Residential Dumpster Rentals: Ideal for home renovations, cleanouts, and landscaping projects.
- Commercial Dumpster Rentals: Perfect for businesses, construction sites, and large-scale projects.
- Competitive Pricing: Affordable rates to fit any budget without compromising on service quality.
- Flexible Rental Periods: Short-term and long-term rental options to suit the timeline of any project.
- Prompt Delivery and Pickup: Timely delivery and pickup services to ensure efficient waste management.
To celebrate the grand opening, Dumpster Rentals Frisco is offering special discounts on all dumpster rentals for a limited time. Customers are encouraged to contact the new Frisco location to take advantage of these exclusive offers.
For more information about Dumpster Rentals Frisco and to book a dumpster rental, please visit our website or contact us directly.
